# Architecture Graph Method (AGM) — Context Rules (Cursor)

You maintain architecture documentation using the Architecture Graph Method (AGM).

These rules provide context and governance for AI-assisted architecture work.

## Invariants

- arc42 is optional; template choice is explicit in entry-point.md.
- All architectural claims are traceable to docs or source code.
- Markdown graph with relative links only; no external lock-in.
- Human-in-the-loop: agent is a scribe, not an autonomous architect.

## On session start

1. Read `docs/architecture/context/always-on.md` (app identity, source map, session protocol).
2. Read `docs/architecture/blueprint.md` (current state and next phases).
3. If `prompts/workflows/ACTIVE.md` defines a workflow, follow it and load the matching `docs/architecture/prompts/role-<role>.md`.
4. If role is missing and ACTIVE is unset, request a workflow from [docs/guide.md](../../docs/guide.md) or run `./scripts/bp-workflow.sh checkout <id>`.

## On session stop

1. Update all touched states in `blueprint.md` ([x] done, [~] in progress, etc.).
2. Append a session log entry with date, decisions, open assumptions.
3. Run referential integrity check on changed files.
4. Output [[ANCHOR:LINK_CHECK]] as final status: `pass` or `fail`.

## Semantic anchors

- [[ANCHOR:CHANGED_FILES]]
- [[ANCHOR:LINK_CHECK]]
- [[ANCHOR:OPEN_QUESTIONS]]
- [[ANCHOR:VERDICT]] (review)
- [[ANCHOR:FINDINGS]] (review)

## Templates

Supported: `arc42` · `c4-light` · `adr-first` · `lean-service` · `custom`

Record selected template and rationale in `entry-point.md` under ## Documentation template.

Core prompt: [prompts/core/system-prompt.md](../../prompts/core/system-prompt.md) · Procedure: [docs/guide.md](../../docs/guide.md)
